\n[[Category:Motor Barnaul players]]\n[[Category:Toros Neftekamsk players]]\n\n{{Belarus-icehockey-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=May 2014}}\n{{Infobox ice hockey player\n| name = Nikita Osipov\n| image = \n| caption =\n| image_size = 230px\n| team = [[HC Dinamo Minsk]]\n| league = [[Kontinental Hockey League|KHL]] \n| prospect_team = \n| prospect_league = \n| former_teams = [[HC Sibir Novosibirsk]]\n| ntl_team = Belarus\n| position = [[Forward (ice hockey)|Forward]]\n| shoots = Left\n| height_ft = 6\n| height_in = 0\n| weight_lb = 172\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1984|04|22}}\n| birth_place = [[Samara, Russia|Samara]], [[Russia]]\n| draft = Undrafted\n| career_start = 2002\n| career_end = \n}}\n'''Nikita Osipov''' (born April 22, 1984) is a [[Belarus]]ian [[ice hockey]] player. He is currently playing with the [[HC Dinamo Minsk]] of the [[Kontinental Hockey League]] (KHL).\n\nOsipov played in the KHL with [[HC Sibir Novosibirsk]] during the [[2012\u201313 KHL season|2012\u201313]] season.<ref>http://en.khl.ru/players/91/</ref>\n\n==International==\nOsipov was named to the [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team]] for competition at the [[2014 IIHF World Championship]].<ref>http://www.iihfworlds2014.com/en/news/roster-forming/</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n{| border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"1\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"text-align:center; width:60em\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! colspan=\"3\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Regular season]] \n! rowspan=\"99\" bgcolor=\"#ffffff\" | \n! colspan=\"5\" | [[Playoffs]] \n|- bgcolor=\"#e0e0e0\" \n! [[Season (sports)|Season]] \n! Team \n! League \n! GP \n! [[Goal (ice hockey)|G]] \n! [[Assist (ice hockey)|A]] \n! [[Point (ice hockey)|Pts]] \n! [[Penalty (ice hockey)|PIM]] \n! GP\n! G \n! A \n! Pts \n! PIM \n|- \n| [[2001\u201302 Pervaya Liga season|2001\u201302]]\n| [[HC Dynamo Moscow]]-2\n| [[Supreme Hockey League Championship|Russia3]]\n| 32 || 1