gory:Sportspeople from Oskemen]]\n[[Category:Kazakhstani ice hockey players]]\n[[Category:Soviet ice hockey players]]\n[[Category:Asian Games gold medalists for Kazakhstan]]\n[[Category:Asian Games silver medalists for Kazakhstan]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 1999 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2003 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Medalists at the 2007 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 1999 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 2003 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey players at the 2007 Asian Winter Games]]\n[[Category:Asian Games medalists in ice hockey]]\n[[Category:HC Sibir Novosibirsk players]]\n[[Category:Kazakhmys Satpaev players]]\n[[Category:Kazzinc-Torpedo players\u200e]]\n[[Category:Yertis Pavlodar players]]\n\n\n{{Kazakhstan-icehockey-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Rodw", "label": "safe", "comment": "Disambiguating links toSibir Novosibirsk(link changed toHC Sibir Novosibirsk; link changed toHC Sibir Novosibirsk) usingDisamAssist.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Maxim_Komissarov"}
{"title_page": "Serhiy Pichuhin", "text_new": "'''Serhiy Pichuhin''' ({{lang-uk|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0456\u0447\u0443\u0433\u0456\u043d}}; {{lang-ru|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u041f\u0438\u0447\u0443\u0433\u0438\u043d}}; born 13 March 1961) is a Ukrainian Olympics sailor that represented the Unified Team in the 1992 Summer Olympics and Ukraine in the 1996 and 2000 Summer Olympics.<ref>https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pi/serhiy-pichuhin-1.html</ref>\n{{Footer World Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer Winners Vintage Yachting Games}}\n{{Footer Italian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer Austrian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer German Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer Hungarian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Pichuhin, Serhiy}}\n[[Category:Ukrainian male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of the Unified Team]]\n[[Category:Soviet male sailors (sport)]]\n[[Category:Olympic sailors of Ukraine]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1992 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 1996 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:Sailors at the 2000 Summer Olympics \u2013 Soling]]\n[[Category:European Champions Soling]]\n[[Category:Soling class world champions]]\n", "text_old": "'''Serhiy Pichuhin''' ({{lang-uk|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0456\u0439 \u041f\u0456\u0447\u0443\u0433\u0456\u043d}}; {{lang-ru|\u0421\u0435\u0440\u0433\u0435\u0439 \u041f\u0438\u0447\u0443\u0433\u0438\u043d}}; born 13 March 1961) is a Ukrainian Olympics sailor that represented the Unified Team in the 1992 Summer Olympics and Ukraine in the 1996 and 2000 Summer Olympics.<ref>https://www.sports-reference.com/olympics/athletes/pi/serhiy-pichuhin-1.html</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n{{Footer World Champions Soling}}\n{{Footer Winners Vintage Yachting Games}}\n{{Footer Italian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Footer Austrian Championship Winners in Soling}}\n{{Foo